:filter:ignore
/Filter [off|<users>]   Filter users
The filter command activates a message filter to prevent you from
annoying messages of your very special friends. <users> is a list of
calls, separated with blanks. "/filter" without an argument given
displays the current status of the filter, "/filter off" will deactivate
it, "/filter -" or "/filter @" too.
:filterwords
/FILTERWords [off|word] Filter bad words
The filterwords command will filter messages containing bad words.
:filtermsgs
/FILTERMsgs [arg]       Filter private or channel msgs
Filtermsgs does finetuning on private and channel messages to you.
Values are bitwise ORed, for ignoring:
  private msgs from  1: users  4: conversd
  channel            2: users  8: conversd
A value of 0 means no filtering (default).
Do not filter conversd messages if there is not *really* a reason for.
Filtermsgs without arg shows the current status. The status is
automaticaly stored in your /profile.
