:history
/HIstory [-] [chan] [n] Show / remove history on channel

A history of the last messages on the channel (i.e. before you joined in)
could be seen with the /history command.

Without arg, chan defaults to the current channel, and n defaults
to 16 lines. Thus, you mostly will just say /history.

chan may be any channel number you currently are on.
chan '*' refers to the current channel. chan "all" is for sysop
use only.

The third argument is the ammount of lines. If ommited, the last 16 lines
of the channel are displayed.
With n = 0 or n = "all", every stored line is sent.
With n = -10 the last 10 lines are displayed. With n = +5, the first 5
lines are sent. With n = 3, the _last_ three lines are sent (because this
is the most wanted request).

chan could be ommited, if you say /history -10 or /history +5.

With "/history -" or "/history delete" you could delete the history for
the current channel. With "/history - 1" you delete the history for
channel 1.  Please note, that you need to be channel-op for deleting
the history.

On invisible and secret channels, there's no channel history.

Messages older than n hours are automaticaly deleted from the history.
If a channel becomes empty, the history will be expunged.
Only the last n lines are stored for /history.
The expire time and number of stored lines depend on the site
configuration.
